correctness.rationale: The extraction has multiple factual errors, schema issues, and ungrounded/placeholder values, and it mixes conditions from different samples, breaking process coherence. Key problems: (1) Schema/structural violations and nulls: plasmaPower is set to null (schema expects an object or omit if not PEALD); many fields use placeholders or zero values (opticalProperties, resistivity, carrierDensity, subthresholdSwing, onOffRatio, safety, roughness, filmDensity, uniformity, conformality), which violates the no-null/empty requirement. Several processParameters (saturation, nucleationPeriod, dosingTime, purgeTime, flowRates) are nested under thicknessControl instead of at the processParameters level as defined in the schema. (2) Pressure incorrect: value 1.96 mmHg is taken from a DEZ partial pressure of 1.96 mbar (not reactor pressure) and with wrong unit conversion; the reactor operates at atmospheric pressure. (3) Growth per cycle errors: ZnO GPC is reported as 0.18 Å/cycle, but the article states 0.18 nm/cycle (~1.8 Å). A single GPC value for InGaZnO is not supported (GPC decreases with In+Ga content). (4) SupercycleDesign inappropriate: article uses coinjection of metal precursors in SALD, not compositional supercycles; the 1:1:1 subcycles and sequence are unsupported. (5) Composition wrong: atomicRatio set to 1:1:1 is not reported; elemental concentration 23% corresponds to In in IZO (not IGZO). For the IGZO TFT example, the article gives In 20% and Ga 8% (at.% of cations). (6) Device/film incoherence: filmThickness 60 nm after 1400 cycles corresponds to growth study conditions, while device metrics (μ_FE ≈ 3.5 cm^2/V·s, onset ~ -25 V) refer to a 15 nm IGZO film; mixing these into one process breaks traceability/coherence. (7) Threshold voltage misassigned: the text cites an onset voltage of -25 V for the specific device; V_th is not explicitly -25 V. (8) Purging gas set to Argon without support; SALD doesn’t use time-based purge steps here. (9) Uniformity 0%, conformality aspect ratio 0, roughness 0, film density 0 are unjustified. Properties to correct/review: processParameters.pressure; thicknessControl.growthPerCycle values and units; remove/disable supercycleDesign; materialProperties.filmComposition (both elementalConcentration and atomicRatio) to match IGZO data (e.g., In 20%, Ga 8%); align filmThickness/numberofCycles with the device sample or drop device metrics for the 60 nm sample; deviceProperties.thresholdVoltage; remove unsupported purgingGas; place dosing/purge/flow fields at correct schema level; eliminate null/placeholder/zero entries or provide grounded values.

completeness.rationale: The extraction is largely incomplete and contains multiple schema violations and factual inconsistencies. Key issues: (1) Schema violations and placeholders: several fields are null or placeholder text (plasmaPower=None; opticalProperties=None; subthresholdSwing=None; onOffRatio=None; reactor name/manufacturer='Not Found'), which violates the object-type requirements and the no-empty-values guideline. (2) Pressure mis-specified: the value 1.96 with unit MilliM_HG is taken from a DEZ partial pressure in mbar, not the reactor pressure, and with an incorrect unit conversion/assignment. (3) Growth-per-cycle wrong: ZnO GPC is reported as ~0.18 nm/cycle in the article, but the extraction lists 0.18 Å (10× too small) and assigns the same value to IGZO, contrary to the article stating IGZO/IZO GPC is lower. (4) Supercycle design incorrectly added: the article used SALD with coinjection of metal precursors, not a supercycle sequence; the provided subcycle counts/sequence are not traceable. (5) Film thickness inconsistencies: the process film thickness is set to 60 nm after 1400 cycles, which corresponds to InZnO conditions (high TMIn/DEZ) and not necessarily IGZO; the device films are explicitly 15 nm a-IGZO but that process is not represented. (6) Missing/incorrect composition: the atomic ratio 'In:Ga:Zn = 1:1:1' is not reported; the article provides compositions such as In=20% and Ga=8% (sum 28%) for the TFT example; the single 23% value is ambiguous (In in IZO) and not a complete IGZO composition. (7) Uniformity, conformality, roughness, and film density are filled with zero or placeholder values without support from the text. (8) Device properties: the -25 V value is an onset voltage for one device, not necessarily the threshold; on/off ratio and subthreshold swing are missing yet set to None (invalid). (9) Dosing/purge/flows: only one dosing time is provided (120 ms) labeled for 'InGaZnO'; the article reports a range (20–120 ms) and constant 120 ms for some experiments; purgeTime and flowRates are empty, and purgingGas=Argon is not evidenced. (10) Multiple processes in the article (ZnO, InZnO, IGZO and the specific 15 nm IGZO TFT) are not separated into distinct, coherent process objects. Properties to add/review: correct reactor pressure (or omit if not provided), correct GPC units/values, remove unsupported supercycle design, include the 15 nm IGZO TFT deposition as a separate process (with 120 ms exposures and reported composition In 20%, Ga 8%), provide traceable composition entries, and remove null/placeholder fields or populate them with article-backed values.
